gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pacers 142, Bucks 130
gameRecap.excerpt: The Pacers defeated the Bucks, 142-130. Tyrese Haliburton led the way for the Pacers with 31 points (5-11 3pt. FG), 12 assists, three blocks and zero turnovers, while Bennedict Mathurin added 16 points and three assists in the victory. Giannis Antetokounmpo (26 points, 11 rebounds, eight assists) and Damian Lillard (23 points, five assists) combined for 49 points for the Bucks in the losing effort. The Pacers have won their fifth consecutive game as they improve to 19-14 on the season, while the Bucks fall to 24-10.
